# Description
The Portfolio Webpage is a personal website designed to showcase an individual's skills, projects, and professional information. It acts as an online resume that highlights achievements, technical skills, and completed work. The portfolio helps others, such as recruiters or clients, understand the person's abilities and experience.
# Objective
The main objectives of this project are:
To create a personal portfolio using HTML and CSS
To showcase skills, projects, and personal information
To design a clean and professional layout
To improve web design and development skills
To create a responsive webpage that works on all devices
# Key Sections of Portfolio Website
1. Home Section
Displays name and introduction
Shows professional title (Example: Web Developer, Student, Designer)
2. About Section
Provides personal information
Includes education, background, and career goals
3. Skills Section
Shows technical skills such as HTML, CSS, JavaScript, etc.
Helps employers understand your abilities
4. Projects Section
Displays completed projects
Shows project names, descriptions, and screenshots
5. Contact Section
Provides contact information such as email, phone, or social media
6. Footer Section
Shows copyright information
Contains additional links if needed
# Technologies Used
HTML5 – for webpage structure
CSS3 – for styling and layout
Media Queries – for responsive design
# Responsiveness
The portfolio webpage is designed to be responsive, meaning it adjusts properly on mobile phones, tablets, and desktop screens for better user experience.
# Conclusion
The Portfolio Webpage project helps in creating a professional online presence. It is useful for showcasing skills, projects, and experience. This project also improves knowledge of HTML, CSS, and responsive web design, which are essential skills for web development.


